# 4. 夢の終わり

An's Father: Taiga!
Taiga: Hey, Ken.
An's Father: A customer just told me what happened.
An's Father: You really went through with it?
Taiga: What did I say? I didn't want to leave any loose ends.
An's Father: I see.
Taiga: I also told them about Nagi.
An's Father: ...!
Taiga: They need to know if they're gonna “succeed” us.
Taiga: But I only told them a few things. You'll have to tell them the rest... Right?
An's Father: Yeah, I know.
An: ...
Arata: ...
Toya: ...! Tono!
Toya: Tono, where are you going...?
Arata: Where...?
Arata: I'm going home. There's nothing left for me here.
Akito: Wait, what do you mean by that...?
Arata: I mean, didn't you see just now?
Arata: There's no way we can do better than that.
Kohane: Oh...
Kotaro: T-Tono...
Akito: And you're okay with that...?
Akito: You aren't, are you...? I thought you were willing to do whatever it took...!
Arata: I wasn't able to respond...
Arata: All I had to say was, “Taunt me all you want! I'll keep carrying his dreams!”
Akito: ...!
Akito: But still...!
Akito: That's...
Arata: I had no idea what to say in that moment. I drew a complete blank...
Toya: ...
Arata: Anyway, well...
Arata: This is it for me.
Akito: ...!
Arata: I'll see you all... No...
Arata: Goodbye. This team was fun while it lasted...
Toya: Tono...!
Akito: ...!
Tatsuya: ...
Tatsuya: I'm not gonna lie. This feels like the end of the line...
Kotaro: What...?! You're not also...?!
Tatsuya: I... We never had a problem with losing to anyone.
Tatsuya: Because we knew that we could fight again another day. At least, that's what we believed...
Tatsuya: But today, we saw reality...
Tatsuya: There are actually people out there who can't be beaten no matter how hard you try...
Kohane: Oh...
Kohane: This is terrifying...
Kohane: ...
Tatsuya: Also, if... Even if we manage to outdo Taiga someday...
Tatsuya: I'm having a hard time seeing us surpassing RAD WEEKEND...
Tatsuya: I just don't know how we can...
Toya: But...
Tatsuya: I honestly didn't want to see things end like this...
Tatsuya: But I think it's time that I grew up and gave up on this dream...
Tatsuya: So, bye...
Kotaro: Why's this happening...?
Kotaro: This... This isn't fair! Not one bit...!
Kotaro: Why?! Just why...?! This was the first real dream I've ever had... Why did it have to be impossibly hard...?!
Kotaro: Why...?! Why...?! Why couldn't I sing when it really mattered...?
Kotaro: Why...? Why am I such a stupid, spineless piece of garbage...?!
Akito: Mita...
Kotaro: *Sob* *Cry*
Kotaro: ...
Kotaro: What Taiga said...
Kotaro: Did he mean we shouldn't chase after dreams we can't possibly achieve...?
Kohane: ...! No, that's...!
Kotaro: I was holding you all back... I knew this entire time...
Kotaro: But I clung to how you guys were all chasing after the same dream as me...
Kotaro: I didn't want to let go of that... Which was probably really bad...
Toya: No, Mita, don't say that!
Kotaro: Sorry, you guys...
Kotaro: I'm really sorry...
Kohane: Mita!
Akito: ...!
Akito: Dammit...!
???: There you are!
An: Dad...?
Toya: Ken...?! What are you doing here...?
An's Father: I heard from one of my customers...and Taiga.
An's Father: He told you didn't he...? About Nagi?
Kohane: ...!
An: ... Yeah, he did.
An: So, you also knew...?
An: You knew this whole time and didn't tell me...?
An's Father: An...
An: ... Why?
An: Why?! Why?!
An: Why was I the only one who didn't know something this important?!
An: None of this makes any sense! I thought everybody was on my side! We were all like family!
An: Seriously, why?! I don't get it! Why only me...?!
An's Father: Because that's what Nagi wanted.
An: Ugh! I don't care!
An: That doesn't explain anything at all!!!
An's Father: ... I'm sorry, An.
An's Father: Let's talk about this more at our place.
An's Father: Including you, Akito, Toya, Kohane... We'll need you all to join us.
An's Father: Today, I'll tell you everything. About how and why RAD WEEKEND happened...
An's Father: I flipped the sign to say closed, so no one else should be bothering us.
An's Father: This is going to take some time, so please sit down and make yourselves comfortable.
Kohane: Okay...
An's Father: Where do I begin? I don't actually know exactly what Taiga told you all...
An's Father: But Nagi is gone, and that's the truth.
An: ...
An's Father: I'm sure you all have a long list of questions you'd like to ask.
An's Father: So, please allow me to tell you everything, from the beginning to the end. Who Nagi was and how RAD WEEKEND came to be.
An's Father: And first... Well, you need to know more about Nagi. About us, RADder.
An's Father: We first decided to form a team together when were in junior high.
An's Father: Taiga and I went to the same school, but we didn't really get along at first. Him singing was the reason I actually began hanging out around here...
Akito: (Oh...)
Taiga: One day, Ken walked by while I was doing a street performance... He gave me this look of boredom which really bothered me.
Taiga: I thought, “Hey, don't ignore me! You know I'm here! Isn't there anything you feel passionate about?!”
Taiga: So, I began singing like there was no tomorrow.
Taiga: My performance definitely sparked something inside him. It was pretty obvious.
Akito: (He's probably talking about that...)
An's Father: We fought, sang, fought, sang... Then, one day, this girl suddenly appeared, clinging to Taiga. That was when I met Nagi for the first time.
An's Father: She said, “You're the weirdo who's been hanging out with Taiga? Why don't you sing with me too?”
An's Father: She sounded like a piece of work at first... But my impression of her completely changed after I heard her sing.
An's Father: I'd heard rumors that Taiga's little sister was an unbelievable singer... But I was still blown away.
Kohane: You were...?
An's Father: Yes. Despite her small stature, she had this mature singing voice and an uncanny ability to captivate her listeners...
An's Father: I'll never forget that voice...
An: ...
An's Father: And before we knew it, the three of us began hanging out together.
An's Father: Then, one day, Nagi said, “We should form a team. We could rule the world.”
An's Father: As crazy as that sounded at the time... Chasing after the same dream as the two of them sounded pretty nice.
An's Father: A part of me thought that we really could become the best musicians in the world someday.
An's Father: We went over to Crawl Green, the owner gave us his blessing to debut there, and we were given permission to put on an event.
An's Father: After that, scouts from the big labels began following us, and we ended up signing with an agency.
An's Father: We'd finally become professional musicians, but that was only the beginning of our troubles...
An: ...
